    "comment": "Rationale: Subcellular fractionation: CSP was mainly found in the synaptic vesicle fraction (LP2). It was not detectable in cytosolic fractions (S3, LS2), implying that the entire pool of CSP is subject to palmitoylation and membrane bound.\n\nPolyclonal rabbit antibody directed against rat CSP was generated with GST fusion proteins containing full-length CSPa construct. Specificity of the antibody was demonstrated comparing control and CSPa KO mouse brains by Western Blot (Fig.4D).\n\n23/5/2017 Pim\nUniprot states that CSpa is palmitoylated. This and the experimental evidence support the \"anchored component... \" term. Experimental description: Equal amounts of subcellular fractions from rat brain (20 μg/lane) were analyzed with specific antibodies...",
